{title: A Lover's Quarrel}
{artist: George Morgan}
{composer: Written by Newt Richardson and Vic McAlpin}

[3/4 time]
[C]I just had a date that didn’t mean a thing
Cause the girl in my arms wasn’t [G7]you
And the date that I had that made me so sad
Made me [F]care more [G7]darling for [C]you[C7]
[F]We had a quarrel a [C]lover’s quarrel
That [G7]we let tear us [C]apart[C7]
